 RESIDENT doctors in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) on Tuesday began an indefinite strike action over non-payment of COVID-19 hazard and inducement allowances to health workers, among other issues. The Association of Resident Doctors, FCTA reached a decision after its Emergency General Meeting following expiration of a 14-day ultimatum given to the FCT Administration. It noted that despite the sundry promises made to pay the hazard and inducement allowance within the period of the issued ultimatum, it is yet to be paid to health care workers in the various FCT hospitals and the isolation and treatment centres. It, therefore, resolve to begin its indefinite strike from 8am on the 1st of September 2020,until its sundry demands are met. 